README

Form Validation with Dynamic Field Display
This project is a simple form validation example with dynamic field display using HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and jQuery.

Overview
The form consists of several fields that require validation before submission. Additionally, there's a dynamic field that is displayed based on the selection made in another field.

Features
Form Validation: Validates various fields such as Identification Document Number, Passport Number, TIN Number, etc., ensuring that they meet specific criteria.
Dynamic Field Display: Shows/hides the "Specify purpose of importation" field based on the selection made in the "Importation details" field.
How to Use
Clone the Repository:
git clone <git@github.com:AbimanaNuru/Business_form_email.git>
Open index.html in your Browser:
Open the index.html file in your preferred web browser to access the form.

Fill out the Form:
Fill out the form fields. The "Specify purpose of importation" field will be displayed only if "other" is selected in the "Importation details" field.

Submit the Form:
Click on the "Submit" button to submit the form. Validation messages will be displayed if any of the fields are invalid.

